🌀M81 is one of the brightest galaxies in the night sky. This stunning spiral contains a supermassive #BlackHole at its core that's 70 million times more massive than our Sun, or about 16 times more massive than Sagittarius A*, the black hole in the center of our Milky Way Galaxy. 

📱Get this #beautiful #pic as a #background #wallpaper for your phone or tablet: https://chandra.harvard.edu/instagram/wallpaper/

